# Methodology Routing Matrix

## Default Order

1. Check `project_develop_policy.md`.
2. Run Agent Room executor routing for any two-or-more-agent request.
3. Pick the primary methodology.
4. Select agents.
5. Record new agent personas when needed.
6. Execute work.
7. Verify and record results.

## Routing Table

| Case Type | Primary Method | Supporting Agents | Required Record |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| New feature idea or behavior change | Superpowers brainstorming | product-manager, game-developer, ui-designer | `Planner/` or `Developer/agent_room/` |
| Implementation plan | Superpowers writing-plans | agent-room-executor, game-developer, mobile-developer | `Developer/agent_room/` or `docs/superpowers/plans/` if requested |
| Code implementation | Superpowers TDD or ce-work | frontend-developer, mobile-developer, game-developer | `Developer/` |
| Code review | Compound Engineering ce-code-review | reviewer, code-reviewer, security-auditor when needed | `Quaility_Assurance/` |
| Product or CEO review | g-stack CEO/product review or product-manager | product-manager, risk-manager | `CEO/` |
| Gameplay/content rules | Project Planner policy | game-developer, product-manager | `Planner/` |
| Graphics or visual QA | Graphic policy plus g-stack/browser validation | graphic_designer, ui-designer, qa-expert | `Graphic_designer/`, `Quaility_Assurance/` |
| Mobile/touch runtime behavior | Superpowers TDD plus g-stack/browser validation | mobile-developer, reviewer, qa-expert | `Developer/`, `Quaility_Assurance/` |
| Debugging | Superpowers systematic-debugging or ce-debug | debugger, reviewer, relevant specialist | `Developer/`, `Quaility_Assurance/` |
| Knowledge compounding | Compound Engineering ce-compound | reviewer, documentation-engineer | `docs/solutions/` |

## Superpowers Integration

Use Superpowers when the task is about:

- brainstorming
- requirements shaping
- implementation planning
- TDD
- systematic debugging
- verification before completion
- subagent-driven development

Agent Room rule: if Superpowers is active, subagents must follow the active Superpowers gate instead of replacing it.

## Compound Engineering Integration

Use Compound Engineering when the task is about:

- structured work execution
- code review
- resolving PR feedback
- compounding a solved problem
- simplifying recent code
- release/PR-quality engineering workflow

Agent Room rule: if Compound Engineering is active, agents must produce outputs that fit its review or compounding structure.

## g-stack Integration

Use g-stack when the task is about:

- project-required Claude/g-stack checks
- `/qa`, `/review`, `/ship`, `/investigate`, or equivalent g-stack workflows
- browser/runtime validation already documented in project QA records
- CEO/product review style when the user asks for g-stack review

Agent Room rule: g-stack is not ignored just because Codex subagents are available. If the case matches a g-stack gate, the executor must name that gate.

## Project Policy Integration

`project_develop_policy.md` outranks Agent Room.

If project policy says a record belongs in a role folder, the final record goes there even if the agent discussion starts in `Developer/agent_room/`.

